<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
    <!-- v1.8.2: the helper bundle has NO sandbox.  It runs as
         launchd-spawned root so it can spawn /usr/sbin/installer.
         The helper's narrow attack surface comes from:
           - SMAuthorizedClients (Info.plist) gating connections
             to the signed app only
           - Authorization-rights re-validation in HelperService
             (defence-in-depth)
           - The SplynekHelperProtocol's typed argument set
             (no shell-string passthrough)

         App Sandbox would prevent the helper from spawning
         system tooling, defeating its purpose.  Same posture
         every other Apple-recommended SMJobBless helper takes. -->
</dict>
</plist>
